extendedInfo.description: Experience true cloud printing! Print seamlessly from your Android to your own connected cloud printer from mobile with ThinPrint Cloud Printer. Benefit from over 10 years of experience in professional printing solutions with more than 3.5 million users worldwide. Get Your Printer Connected. HIGHLIGHTSâ¢ 100% free for personal use: No Ads or in-app purchasesâ¢ Full compatibility: Works with any brand of printerâ¢ Print from all your devices: Print to your cloud printer from your smartphone, tablet or even your laptop â¢ Simple one-time setup: Just a few clicks to print mobile thanks to the ThinPrint Cloud Printer Connector â¢ Share your cloud printer: Easily share your printer with your team and familyFeatures of ThinPrint Cloud Printer for Androidâ¢ Convenient file picker enables printing files from SD and internal storageâ¢ Print from third-party apps via share with ThinPrint Cloud Printerâ¢ Print mobile from anywhere, anytime to your connected cloud printerâ¢ Print any printable file format from your mobile phone or tabletFor more information see our app video or visit http://cloudprinter.thinprint.com.Note on registering: If you do not receive a confirmation e-mail in your inbox after submitting your registration request, it could be because your provider blocks automatically sent e-mails. In this case, please check your spam folder, or try registering with a different e-mail address.Note on network printing / stand alone printers: ThinPrint Cloud Printer does not support network printing via wifi. If you want to print to any printer in your network try our free app Cortado Workplace. It is free and available on Google play: http://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.cortado.androidThinPrint Cloud Printer lets you print from mobile to any brand of printer eg. Samsung, Sharp, Toshiba, HP, Lexmark, Canon, Brother, Epson, Lenovo and many more. Cortado is also the founder of the Cloud Printing Alliance, which is supported by Brother, Dell, Kyocera, Samsung, Kodak, Sharp, Lexmark and Toshiba. Goal of this partnership is to make mobile printing easy.

reviews.comment: Successfully registered at the Cortado Workplace website, installed the Thinprint Connector on both my laptop which is connected to my printer via USB, and my Galaxy Note 8.0 tablet. I pull up a webpage (and I\'ve tried several different ones, to ensure it wasn\'t the fault of the page), and then from my tablet I \"share to\" the ThinPrint Cloud Printer\" and then NOTHING HAPPENS! The icon in my system tray says \"Processing Print Job\" forever until it times out and tells me \"Unable to complete print job.\" Also, no matter what webpage I\'m trying to print it says it\'s printing \"temp.html\", and that seems odd... no unique page names to differentiate print jobs? Meanwhile, my tablet is notifying that ThinPrint successfully completed printing \"temp.html\". Yeah, right! Frustrated beyond words! I thought this was supposed to be slick and seamless?! The Galaxy Note 8.0 is a pretty newly released tablet though... Maybe ThinPrint just hasn\'t kept up with the latest devices? Bummer. I had high hopes based on all the great reviews.
reviews.author: Lisa Davis
